node.text: Throwback to this year's Summer Academy to Inspire Learning (SAIL), a pre-college program at the UO intended to inspire middle and high school students from low socioeconomic, first-generation and underrepresented backgrounds from across the state. By providing first-hand experiences with faculty, volunteers, college student mentors and university campus resources, the program's goal is to get these students interested in pursuing, enrolling and succeeding in higher education.
